description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity within the Macmillan Renton Unit has arisen for a 12 month fixed term secondment to cover maternity leave.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate should have proven post registration experience. This would be a perfect opportunity for those wanting to expandand enhance any transferable skills they have and apply them within the Macmillan Renton Unit. Ideally the candidate should have had experience with CVC lines, cannulation, venepuncture and enhanced communication. You will need to have sound leadership skills, excellent communication and organisational skills and the ability to foster good working relationships, offering care in a kind and compassionate manner. The ideal candidate will be progressive thinking with the ability to work autonomously with support from the multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cancer Services are provided in the Macmillan Renton Unit (MRU). The building was a joint collaboration between the NHS and Macmillan and provides outpatient appointments, chemotherapy and radiotherapy services. WVT provides care for patients with cancers working collaboratively with visiting Oncologists from Gloucester Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust (GHNFT) and Wye Valley NHS Trust Consultants. This post holder will be required to work with and support both teams throughout the patient pathway.&lt;/p&gt;
